Should Schools Provide Free Pads and Tampons?

Have you ever experienced period shaming, or â€œperiod poverty"? Should schools step in to help? Should schools be required to provide free pads and tampons to students? How are pads and tampons similar to toilet paper, soap, Band-Aids and other products that are already provided in schools? How are they different?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: schools should provide some kind of period supplies to students, especially teenagers who are experiencing menstrual cycles.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If schools provide toilet paper, soap and Band-Aids, why not period products?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Adults are expected to provide their own supplies, which is fine.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are too young to be expected to be able to provide for themselves.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If it's about financial reasons, then the school district needs to make sure to make funding for something like this available.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Another reason could be it is uncomfortable for parents.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The more awareness that is brought to periods, the more likely schools are going to start providing them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Just like the nurse's office, bathrooms, books and pencils.
